Package com.rb.nonbiz.jsonapi

Class RangeJsonApiConverter

java.lang.Object
com.rb.nonbiz.jsonapi.RangeJsonApiConverter
All Implemented Interfaces:
HasJsonApiDocumentation
public class RangeJsonApiConverter
extends java.lang.Object
implements HasJsonApiDocumentation
Convert a Range back and forth to JSON for our public API.

Note that this only converts ranges that *include* any endpoints they may have. That is, (-inf, inf), [1, inf), (-inf, 10] and [1, 10] can all be converted because their boundary points are included.

Conversely, ranges that *exclude* an endpoint cannot be converted here. E.g. converting ranges such as (-inf, 10), (1, inf), (1, 10], [1, 10) is not supported here.

Note that our notation is not entirely clear, because we use "closed" when refering to both ranges and individual boundaries. We use ClosedRange to mean a range with both a lower bound and an upper bound, with both bounds being "closed" (e.g. inclusive). We also refer to a range with only one boundary (e.g. Range.atLeast(1), Range.atMost(10)) as having a "closed" bound.

In order to convert a ClosedRange to JSON, use RBJsonObjects.closedRangeToJsonObject(com.google.common.collect.Range<C>, java.util.function.Function<C, com.google.gson.JsonElement>).

See Also:
ClosedRange, RBJsonObjects.closedRangeToJsonObject(com.google.common.collect.Range<C>, java.util.function.Function<C, com.google.gson.JsonElement>)
